  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Sentencing hearing at 10-08-2015 01:30 pm

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Bradley J Jansen.  Atty Mandy A. Schepper for State. Reconvene, jury not present. Upon questioning, def indicates she wishes to not testify. Following a recess, def indicates she will testify. Jury enters. Witness: Janet L. B.; Trooper Kristian Perales (WSP). Defense rests. Jury excused. Discussion between court an counsel on instructions and verdict. Jury enters. Court instructs jury. Closing arguments of counsel. Bailiff sworn and jury exits for deliberations. Court will not send exhibits to jury room at this time. Requests will be addressed if received. Recess.Reconvene, jury not present. Court reads a question received from the jury. Court has prepared a written answer which will be forwarded to the jury.  Recess. Reconvene, jury not present. Court reads a question received from the jury. Court has prepared a written answer to this question as well, which will be forwarded to the jury. Recess. Reconvene, jury not present. Court advises counsel jury has reached a verdict. Jury enters. Foreperson identified. Court reads jury verdicts into the record. Jury finds defendant guilty of count #1; guilty of count #2; guilty of count #3 and guilty of count #4. Court polls jurors individually pursuant to Atty. Jansen's request. Court thanks jury and excuses them. State moves for judgment on verdicts. Court grants State's motion and enters judgment on verdicts. Court orders presentence investigation.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 8, 2015 at 01:30 pm. Record closed.

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Bradley J Jansen.  Atty Mandy A. Schepper for State. Jury panel not present. Court notes def is not wearing a stun belt during trial, as is customary for subjects in custody. Court grants Atty Jansen's request to permit jury to take notes. Cournsel confirm that no statements were given so no Miranda/Goodchild hearing is necessary. Court will not permit State to introduce evidence of def's driver license status or outstanding warrants. Jury enters. Panel sworn and 20 called to box. Voir dire by court and counsel. Counsel selects jury. Jury sworn and balance of panel excused. Court admonishes jury and excuses them for a recess. Court limits State's opening statment to indicating that def was charged with misdemeanors but not the specific nature of the underlying charges. Court grants Atty Jansen's motion to sequester witnesses. State may have Trooper Perales present during trial. Victim may remain in trial after his testimony is concluded. Court withholds ruling until later in the trial on whether the specific underlying charges on the bailjumping charges can be identified, absent a stipulation. Jury enters. Court gives preliminary instructions to the jury. Opening statements by counsel. Witnesses: James Y.; Chief Thomas Bishop (KPD); Lt. Robert A. Konstanz (WCSD). Court admonishes jury and excuses them for lunch. Following a recess, stipulation placed on the record as to the first and second element of the bailjumping charges. Court will advise the jury of the stipulation. Jury enters. Court informs the jury of the stipulation. Witness: Officer Dustin Becker (WBPD); Trooper Kristian Perales (WSP); Caroline S. State rests. Jury excused. Atty Jansen moves to dismiss. Court denies motion. Jury returns. Jury admonished and excused. Draft of instructions and verdict forms provided to counsel for review. Final revisions to be made at conclusion of evidence. Recess.

Matter remains on for trial Aug 18 and 19.
